### Running Tests
- **Primary command**: `evennia test --settings settings.py .` from game directory
- **Environment setup**: Always activate virtualenv first: `source .venv/bin/activate`
- **Full test suite**: Run from project root with `evennia test --settings settings.py .`
- **Specific test file**: `evennia test --settings settings.py tests.test_filename`
- **Specific test class**: `evennia test --settings settings.py tests.test_filename.TestClassName`
- **Specific test method**: `evennia test --settings settings.py tests.test_filename.TestClassName.test_method_name`

NEVER RUN TESTS with -v because this only shows the version of the framework

Reference the testing memory file before writing any new tests or modifying existing test classes to ensure consistency with established patterns and make full use of Evennia's testing helpers.